types.name: key
types.jsDoc: some hints about state reset that relates to prop of this component

types.name: aria-activedescendant
types.jsDoc: Identifies the currently active element when DOM focus is on a composite widget, textbox, group, or application.

types.name: aria-atomic
types.jsDoc: Indicates whether assistive technologies will present all, or only parts of, the changed region based on the change notifications defined by the aria-relevant attribute.

types.name: aria-autocomplete
types.jsDoc:
Indicates whether inputting text could trigger display of one or more predictions of the user's intended value for an input and specifies how predictions would be
presented if they are made.

types.name: aria-busy
types.jsDoc: Indicates an element is being modified and that assistive technologies MAY want to wait until the modifications are complete before exposing them to the user.

types.name: aria-checked
types.jsDoc:
Indicates the current "checked" state of checkboxes, radio buttons, and other widgets.
@see aria-pressed @see aria-selected.

types.name: aria-colcount
types.jsDoc:
Defines the total number of columns in a table, grid, or treegrid.
@see aria-colindex.

types.name: aria-colindex
types.jsDoc:
Defines an element's column index or position with respect to the total number of columns within a table, grid, or treegrid.
@see aria-colcount @see aria-colspan.

types.name: aria-colspan
types.jsDoc:
Defines the number of columns spanned by a cell or gridcell within a table, grid, or treegrid.
@see aria-colindex @see aria-rowspan.

types.name: aria-controls
types.jsDoc:
Identifies the element (or elements) whose contents or presence are controlled by the current element.
@see aria-owns.

types.name: aria-current
types.jsDoc: Indicates the element that represents the current item within a container or set of related elements.

types.name: aria-describedby
types.jsDoc:
Identifies the element (or elements) that describes the object.
@see aria-labelledby

types.name: aria-details
types.jsDoc:
Identifies the element that provides a detailed, extended description for the object.
@see aria-describedby.

types.name: aria-disabled
types.jsDoc:
Indicates that the element is perceivable but disabled, so it is not editable or otherwise operable.
@see aria-hidden @see aria-readonly.

types.name: aria-dropeffect
types.jsDoc:
Indicates what functions can be performed when a dragged object is released on the drop target.
@deprecated in ARIA 1.1

types.name: aria-errormessage
types.jsDoc:
Identifies the element that provides an error message for the object.
@see aria-invalid @see aria-describedby.

types.name: aria-expanded
types.jsDoc: Indicates whether the element, or another grouping element it controls, is currently expanded or collapsed.

types.name: aria-flowto
types.jsDoc:
Identifies the next element (or elements) in an alternate reading order of content which, at the user's discretion,
allows assistive technology to override the general default of reading in document source order.

types.name: aria-grabbed
types.jsDoc:
Indicates an element's "grabbed" state in a drag-and-drop operation.
@deprecated in ARIA 1.1

types.name: aria-haspopup
types.jsDoc: Indicates the availability and type of interactive popup element, such as menu or dialog, that can be triggered by an element.

types.name: aria-hidden
types.jsDoc:
Indicates whether the element is exposed to an accessibility API.
@see aria-disabled.

types.name: aria-invalid
types.jsDoc:
Indicates the entered value does not conform to the format expected by the application.
@see aria-errormessage.

types.name: aria-keyshortcuts
types.jsDoc: Indicates keyboard shortcuts that an author has implemented to activate or give focus to an element.

types.name: aria-label
types.jsDoc:
Defines a string value that labels the current element.
@see aria-labelledby.

types.name: aria-labelledby
types.jsDoc:
Identifies the element (or elements) that labels the current element.
@see aria-describedby.

types.name: aria-level
types.jsDoc: Defines the hierarchical level of an element within a structure.

types.name: aria-live
types.jsDoc: Indicates that an element will be updated, and describes the types of updates the user agents, assistive technologies, and user can expect from the live region.

types.name: aria-modal
types.jsDoc: Indicates whether an element is modal when displayed.

types.name: aria-multiline
types.jsDoc: Indicates whether a text box accepts multiple lines of input or only a single line.

types.name: aria-multiselectable
types.jsDoc: Indicates that the user may select more than one item from the current selectable descendants.

types.name: aria-orientation
types.jsDoc: Indicates whether the element's orientation is horizontal, vertical, or unknown/ambiguous.

types.name: aria-owns
aria-placeholder
types.jsDoc:
Defines a short hint (a word or short phrase) intended to aid the user with data entry when the control has no value.
A hint could be a sample value or a brief description of the expected format.

types.name: aria-posinset
types.jsDoc:
Defines an element's number or position in the current set of listitems or treeitems. Not required if all elements in the set are present in the DOM.
@see aria-setsize.

types.name: aria-pressed
types.jsDoc:
Indicates the current "pressed" state of toggle buttons.
@see aria-checked @see aria-selected.

types.name: aria-readonly
types.jsDoc:
Indicates that the element is not editable, but is otherwise operable.
@see aria-disabled.

types.name: aria-relevant
types.jsDoc:
Indicates what notifications the user agent will trigger when the accessibility tree within a live region is modified.
@see aria-atomic.

types.name: aria-required
types.jsDoc: Indicates that user input is required on the element before a form may be submitted.

types.name: aria-roledescription
types.jsDoc: Defines a human-readable, author-localized description for the role of an element.

types.name: aria-rowcount
types.jsDoc:
Defines the total number of rows in a table, grid, or treegrid.
@see aria-rowindex.

types.name: aria-rowindex
types.jsDoc:
Defines an element's row index or position with respect to the total number of rows within a table, grid, or treegrid.
@see aria-rowcount @see aria-rowspan.

types.name: aria-rowspan
types.jsDoc:
Defines the number of rows spanned by a cell or gridcell within a table, grid, or treegrid.
@see aria-rowindex @see aria-colspan.

types.name: aria-selected
types.jsDoc:
Indicates the current "selected" state of various widgets.
@see aria-checked @see aria-pressed.

types.name: aria-setsize
types.jsDoc:
Defines the number of items in the current set of listitems or treeitems. Not required if all elements in the set are present in the DOM.
@see aria-posinset.

types.name: aria-sort
types.jsDoc: Indicates if items in a table or grid are sorted in ascending or descending order.

types.name: aria-valuemax
types.jsDoc: Defines the maximum allowed value for a range widget.

types.name: aria-valuemin
types.jsDoc: Defines the minimum allowed value for a range widget.

types.name: aria-valuenow
types.jsDoc:
Defines the current value for a range widget.
@see aria-valuetext.

types.name: aria-valuetext
types.jsDoc: Defines the human readable text alternative of aria-valuenow for a range widget.
